Class OpSHA1

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.eternitywall.ots.op.Op

          • com.eternitywall.ots.op.OpSHA1
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Op>

    public class OpSHA1
extends OpCrypto
    Cryptographic SHA1 operation Cryptographic operation tag numbers taken from RFC4880, although it's not guaranteed that they'll continue to match that RFC in the future. Remember that for timestamping, hash algorithms with collision attacks *are* secure! We've still proven that both messages existed prior to some point in time - the fact that they both have the same hash digest doesn't change that. Heck, even md5 is still secure enough for timestamping... but that's pushing our luck...
